messages.text: Dad!!
Amber! Oh thank God.
How did you escape? Didn’t the chief go after you?
Dad!! Dad don’t move I brought a med kit. Oh my god…dad.
There’s so much blood...
Yeah. Asshole knew to shoot around the Kevlar.
But it’s fine. Just my shoulder. Agh!
Dad…
Sweetie I need you to focus right now. Just come help me up. Let’s go. Now.
But aren’t you supposed to stay still? We need to try and stop the bleeding.
Amber! We have no idea who might be coming here to clean up this mess.
We have to act fast.
Okay. Take it slow now. This is gonna hurt…
Agh! Goddammit!
Yeah I told you!
Ugh. Let’s get to the car.
Okay.
And we do know who this was.
It’s Luke. Luke is behind this.
Who?
From my school dad. Luke.
You kidding me? How is this all him?
I don’t know, but somehow.
This is the chief’s phone.
Looks like they were feeding info to each other this whole time.
That bastard…
Crooked this whole time. And working with kids?
Yeah he’s a piece of shit.
I mean…if he’s crooked…
Jesus. Who else?
But…
But what?
The chief is gone.
You mean he’s...
Amber are you okay?
Dad. We have to get Luke.
He’s on the run now.
And he is not getting away.
Amber -
I swear to God when I find him I’m gonna -
We can’t take this upon ourselves Amber!
That’s not how we go about this.
And what, you expect me to go to the cops?
I expect you to be level headed.
You have evidence and a name now.
We take this to the officials and —
So another crooked cop can just shoot at us?
We are lucky we’re still alive Amber
And Luke is lucky I haven’t gotten to him yet!
He murdered one of my best friends.
And he tried to kill us both!
There’s no way in hell he’s getting out of this.
If you want to stop me, you’ll have to arrest me.
Jesus Amber.
Calm down for a second.
See that’s your problem dad!
You always think things are just gonna work out
And that justice will always prevail
But where the hell was justice when John was burning alive?
Amber watch your tone -
Where was it when the Chief of effing Police gunned you down and ran after me?
This system isn’t here to help dad.
And I’m not gonna sit around and expect it to.
I’m going with or without you.
Jesus…
Okay Amber.
Here. Help me out of this. You’ve taken a bullet before, right?
Dad what are you doing?! Keep that on!
I’ll feel a lot better knowing that you have it.
You might need it where you’re going.
Dad…
Shit. I hear the sirens.
Okay we gotta go
No.
Huh?
You have to go. I’ll keep these guys busy as long as I can.
But dad they’ll -
Amber do not argue with me anymore!
Who knows how many screwed up cops there are. I can’t let them get to you.
You know what you have to do. So go do it!
I love you dad.
I love you too sweetie.
LUKE!!!
Luke I know you’re here! Answer me!
Luke I swear
In the back
Surprised I found you? Asshole?
It’s a public monastery Amber. And I assume you still have the chief’s phone.
I would have been pretty disappointed if you didn’t.
Come here for a seco-
Freeze! Luke don’t you move a damn muscle
Oh goodness, would you put that thing down?
Let’s talk for a bit
Not. A muscle.
There’s no walking away from this for you Luke.
Fine, but I want to show you something. You might want to see it.
C’mon, don’t I get any famous last words?
Shame. I figured you would have more to say to him.
What?
John. That was his name, right?
Don’t you dare say his name!
I’m just saying. You’re wasting time aiming at me
When you could be reunited with your friend
You’re lying
Possibly...
But would you ever forgive yourself for not taking the chance to see him one more time?
Move slowly.
Ooo. I like I girl in power. This way.
Now, I don’t want you to be alarmed when you see him.
Things got pretty uh…heated between us a while back.
You really wanna die right now, don’t you?
Oh, pardon me. I was never the best with words growing up.
How long do these stairs spiral for?
We’re almost down.
Luke if I see you try anything before I see John I…
JOHN!!!
John…Oh my God…
John…look at… what they did to you…
How could anybody…
Goodness, pull yourself together. You’ve seen a charred body before.
But then again, maybe those other ones weren’t your friends.
Or breathing.
I don’t…I don’t even understand how.
Yeah, he’s a tough bastard. Figured I would hang on to him.
I’m glad I did.
Why? Why down here?
What the hell could you possibly gain by keeping him down here?!
The upper hand. You see, you might have gotten the chief.
Unfortunate.
But he’s got an entire squad for me to command.
A few of them are probably having their fun tearing apart your father right about now.
Limb, from pathetic limb.
The rest are on the way here.
So even if you shot me, right here and now, you would either get killed
Or tossed in jail for attempting to burn your friend John alive.
John…I’m so sorry I couldn’t help you…
Jesus! Enough about him.
So there’s no way I’m getting out of this.
Not a chance in hell.
Ah, sirens. Looks like your dad didn’t last very long.
Then answer this for me.
Hah, sure.
This place is public right? Still running?
What are you getting at?
Because if it is, those propane tanks behind you are probably full, right?
You wouldn’t dare.
John… I’m so sorry.
You BITCH! WAI-
See you soon, John.
